Markdown is the working format; this one rarely needs a polished export.

## Run this as a Scout automation

To have the prep waiting before each 1:1, set a Scout **Automation** (Automations -> New automation -> Schedule trigger) timed to the recurring 1:1 — for example "30 minutes before my 1:1 with \<name\>." The prompt: "Prep my 1:1 with \<name\>."

### Heartbeat-safe behavior

When this runs unattended (no one present to approve):

- Write the prep card to the workspace and surface it; **do not** send the person a message, book time, or take any approval-gated action.
- Keep personnel-sensitive detail out of any generic outbound content — link to the source instead.
- Treat tentative calendar items as busy.

