## Quality bar — self-check before delivering

- [ ] The person is resolved by name, role, and reporting line via people search.
- [ ] "Since last time" is grounded in sourced activity, not assumed.
- [ ] Follow-ups list both directions, each with an owner and a status.
- [ ] The agenda puts the person's topics before {{ persona.first_name }}'s.
- [ ] The growth/recognition note is specific and tied to real work — not filler praise.
- [ ] No HR-sensitive or labeled content is pasted into the card — summarized and linked instead.
- [ ] If run unattended, no message is sent and no time is booked on the person's behalf.

If any check fails, fix it before delivering.

## Privacy and boundaries

- 1:1 prep touches personnel context. Reading labeled or Confidential HR content elevates the session's sensitivity level — never write it into the plain-text card or a Teams channel. Summarize and link.
- Do not infer or record mood, performance judgments, or personal circumstances that aren't directly observed and sourced.
- Recognition and feedback are {{ persona.first_name }}'s to deliver — the skill drafts them, it never sends.
